  "text": "Both Kubernetes and Grafana implement the Prometheus metrics exposition pattern using the prometheus client_golang library, but with notably different organizational approaches.\n\n**Kubernetes Architecture:**\nKubernetes uses a sophisticated registry-based architecture with version-aware metric management. The core is `KubeRegistry` interface (staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/registry.go), which wraps prometheus.Registry and adds stability tracking, deprecation handling, and metric versioning. The HTTP exposition is handled by `HandlerFor()` and `HandlerWithReset()` functions in staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/http.go that use promhttp.HandlerFor internally.\n\nThe `/metrics` HTTP endpoint is configured at the API server level in staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/routes/metrics.go through `DefaultMetrics` and `MetricsWithReset` route handlers. These install handlers via `legacyregistry.Handler()` from staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/legacyregistry/registry.go, which provides a global registry with handlers that are already instrumented with InstrumentMetricHandler.\n\nKubernetes organizes metric collectors into specialized subdirectories under staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/prometheus/: workqueue (for queue depth and latency metrics), version (for build info), controllers, feature gates, client-go integration, and REST client metrics. Each package registers collectors using the legacyregistry.MustRegister() function, often in init() blocks. The architecture supports custom collectors via the StableCollector interface (staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/collector.go) with BaseStableCollector providing a foundation for implementing custom metric collectors with stability guarantees.\n\n**Grafana Architecture:**\nGrafana takes a simpler, more direct approach to metrics exposition. The `/metrics` endpoint is handled as a middleware in the HTTP server (pkg/api/http_server.go) via the `metricsEndpoint()` function, which checks the request path and uses `promhttp.HandlerFor(hs.promGatherer, ...)` directly from the prometheus/promhttp package with EnableOpenMetrics option.\n\nThe metrics infrastructure is organized through dependency injection via the metrics service (pkg/infra/metrics/service.go). The `ProvideService()` function initializes metrics and calls `initMetricVars()` and `initFrontendMetrics()` which register metrics with the registerer. The service provides both `ProvideRegisterer()` and `ProvideGatherer()` functions that expose the prometheus registry interfaces.\n\nUniquely, Grafana combines multiple metric sources through a `multiRegistry` gatherer that merges metrics from the Kubernetes legacyregistry (for compatibility with Kubernetes metrics patterns) with prometheus.DefaultGatherer. An `addPrefixWrapper` ensures all metrics are prefixed with \"grafana_\" for namespacing, preventing collisions with system metrics.\n\nAll Grafana metrics are defined globally in pkg/infra/metrics/metrics.go as package-level variables (Counters, Gauges, Summaries, Histograms) and registered together in `initMetricVars()` via a single `reg.MustRegister()` call. Wire dependency injection configuration (pkg/infra/metrics/wireset.go) provides the registerer and gatherer to the HTTP server and services.\n\n**Key Differences:**\n- **Kubernetes**: Hierarchical, version-aware metric registration with custom collector framework and stability levels; metrics distributed across component modules\n- **Grafana**: Centralized metric definition and registration; single-pass initialization; uses wrapper gatherers for composition and prefixing\n- **HTTP Setup**: Kubernetes uses a route-based handler installation pattern; Grafana uses middleware-based endpoint handling\n- **Collector Organization**: Kubernetes structures collectors by functional domain (workqueue, version, controllers); Grafana centralizes metrics in a single package\n- **Multi-Registry**: Grafana explicitly composes multiple gatherers; Kubernetes uses a single legacy registry with internal organization"
}

